__label__low vi bruger cookies til at huske dine indstillinger og give dig den bedst mulige oplevelse på sitet. nyheder 112 sport livsstil tv videnskab sex underholdning oversigt kronprinsens tur over storebæltsbroen suser verden rundt nyheder skrevet af administrator | 13.01.15 | 08:47 12.01.15 / 13:59 del på facebook det har vakt opsigt internationalt, at kronprins frederik i weekenden tog turen over storebæltsbroen, selvom den var lukket på grund af storm. europæiske medier som bbc og det franske nyhedsbureau afp har begge sendt nyheden videre. derudover er historien nået til kronprinsesse marys hjemland, hvor det australske nyhedsbureau aap har rapporteret om den royale køretur. samtlige medier har også videregivet hoffets undskyldning på vegne af kronprins frederik. ifølge sund og bælt, selskabet bag storebæltsbroen, var det "grænsende til livsfarligt" at køre over broen, mens den var lukket på grund af den kraftige storm egon, der ramte danmark i weekenden. - det var en forkert beslutning at tage imod muligheden for, at bilen kunne fortsætte, og det beklager kronprinsen, lød det mandag fra lene balleby, der er kommunikations- og pressechef for kongehuset. - kronprinsen er ked af det skete og kan godt forstå, at situationen var med til at skabe yderligere frustrationer og vrede blandt de mennesker, der havde ventet i mange timer på at passere broen, sagde hun. også politiets efterretningstjeneste, pet, har beklaget, at kronprins frederik efterfulgt af livvagter krydsede en lukket storebæltsbro, og pet gennemgår nu proceduren. stormen egon bragte lørdag vindstød op til orkanstyrke, hvilket lammede trafikken flere steder i danmark og lukkede storebæltsbroen. det betød lange ventetider, da broen blev lukket lørdag omkring klokken 14 og først åbnede klokken fire natten til søndag. men kronprinsens bil kørte over klokken 15.15 på vej mod herning og retur klokken 02.53, mens flere hundrede mennesker angiveligt måtte vente på, at broen åbnede igen. /ritzau/ del på facebook twitter e-mail linse raser efter gårsdagens afsnit af familien fra bryggen: totalt til grin! 24-årig kvinde voldtaget på offentligt toilet - vær opmærksom! minister: ulve skal indhegnes i danmark mystisk skuddrama i sønderjysk by: betjente fandt ukendt mand ramt af skud på gaden dagens populære udland fisker fik død kæmpehaj på krogen: fik et chok, da han sprættede maven op 112 jysk mand stod ved kassen i netto, da han spottede ældre kvinde: slog alarm, da hun gik ud mod p-plads sundhed drop salaten! disse 11 overraskende madvarer kan du trygt spise, hvis du vil tabe dig viralt efterladt hund blev fundet af politi: nu griner alle af ejerens geniale trick, der fik hunden til reagere udland kvinde opdager mystisk bil for enden af blind vej - så går den chokerende sandhed op for hende gossip rasmus holdt sin kæreste hemmelig under x factor: nu viser han hende endelig frem sex og samliv hver tredje kvinde får orgasme ved at blive rørt dette sted - og det er ikke tissekonen sundhed ny forskning: folk, der går sent i seng, dør tidligere 112 23-årig kvinde gik ind i telebutik i aarhus - det ville personalet ønske, hun aldrig havde gjort 112 jysk mand skulle i bilka: rystende syn på p-pladsen fik ham straks til at slå alarm dagens.dk dagens gossip linse raser efter gårsdagens afsnit af familien fra bryggen: totalt til grin! mascha vang afslører: sådan mødte jeg min nye kæreste victoria beckham forarger fans med vanvittig kage: ‘du må leve et meget sørgeligt liv’ rasmus holdt sin kæreste hemmelig under x factor: nu viser han hende endelig frem princess natascha hos lægen med sine børn: chokeret over hård besked mascha vang bekymret efter afsløring af kæreste: bliver chikaneret på sociale medier dansk komiker jubler: er blevet far til tvillinger derfor har christopher ikke givet lyd fra sig i flere måneder efter hård skilsmisse: nu er stjerne fra 'badehotellet' smaskforelsket thomas blachman dropper musikken efter x factor finale: det skal han lave nu geggo overrasker fans med vild nyhed: 'derfor har vi taget beslutningen' gravide mille dinesen afslører kønnet på sit kommende barn dansk rapper har friet til sin skuespiller-kæreste: 'han er mit livs kærlighed' x factor får stjernebesøg: hitmager indtager scenen på fredag linse kessler taler ud om sit nye liv i spanien: ‘al start er svær’ medie: dronning margrethe skal alligevel ikke begraves alene mopper er flyttet til spanien med linse efter narkodom: medina skifter navn igen-igen - __label__low skip to content rtsoft wiki user tools log in site tools search toolsshow pagesourceold revisionsbacklinksrecent changesmedia managersitemaplog in> recent changesmedia managersitemap trace: • filemanager proton:filemanager table of contents file handling loading a file into memory base directory vs the user data directory using filemanager directly how to stream a file in mounting a .zip as a filesystem what about writing user data files? file handling first, you can use your good old c fwrite/fread or streams to your heart's content. but there is a reason why you shouldn't - the android file system sort of requires you to load your stuff from a giant zip, and using the filemanager instead hides this ugliness from you. loading a file into memory load any kind of file into memory like this: fileinstance myfile("test.txt"); //a small text file of 5 lines or so logmsg("i just loaded a file into memory that is %d bytes.", myfile.getsize()); logmsg(myfile.getaschars()); that list thing where i display the text file to the output window is only possible because of two things: i know it's a text file i know the filemanager secretly adds a null at the end when allocating memory for the file when the fileinstance object is destroyed as it goes out of scope, it deletes the associated memory it had loaded the file into. base directory vs the user data directory internally, fileinstance and functions like fileexists() are using the filemanager. the filemanager does the following for you behind the scenes: * automatically decompresses files that have been compressed with rtpack (file extension doesn't matter, it checks for a header) * automatically decompresses from a mounted .zip file when appropriate (the asset dir of the .apk in android is automatically mounted for you at init) * adds the base path of your app data, so “interface/some.rtfont” will work on all platforms (it prepends getbaseapppath() for you if needed) there are times when you don't want it to add the base path though, for instance, when saving user data, you should use getsavepath(). here is how we would have loaded the above from the user data directory: fileinstance myfile(getsavepath()+"test.txt", false); that false we send for the bool baddbasepath parm says “don't prepend anything to the path, i know what i'm doing”. it's available when using most file operations. using filemanager directly instead of using fileinstance, you could just do: int filesizebytes; byte *pdata = getfilemanager()->get(getsavepath()+"test.txt", &filesizebytes, true); //operate on data //we have to release the data ourselves or hello memory leak safe_delete_array(pdata); how to stream a file in to insure a hassle free android compile you should use filemanager::getstreaming instead of raw fopen/fread type stuff. it returns a streaminginstance that operates sort of like a fileinstance but actually smartly loads the file as you go, which may even be from a .zip file. why would you want to do this and not just load it all in one chunk? dungeon scroll's word dictionary is over one meg in size. streaming it means i can load 10kb at a time and update a progress bar each frame. example: int size; m_pstreaminginstance = getfilemanager()->getstreaming("some file", &size, false); //m_pstreaminginstance will be null on error //we now have a streaming instance, but we haven't actually loaded any data yet. we'll load directory into our own buffer. char st_buffer[4096]; while (m_pstreaminginstance->readlineoftext(st_buffer, 4096)) { logmsg(st_buffer); } safe_delete(m_pstreaminginstance); notice: we used streaminginstance::readlineoftext but we could have used streaminginstance::read instead for pure data. (it's a lot like fread) it internally cached the file for speed, for instance, if it's actually in a compressed zip and you are asking for one byte at a time it will really be decoding in 4 kb chunks behind the scenes mounting a .zip as a filesystem this happens automatically when you are doing an android target, so you can load resources by filename and not worry about where they actually are. (android wants to keep them in your .apk you used to install) but you may want to mount your own zips for some reason. let's examine how it's done: filesystemzip *pfilesystem = new filesystemzip(); pfilesystem->init("somezip.file")); //i'm not doing error handling in these examples, but it would return false on error //to print out the entire contents of the zip: vector contents = pfilesystem->getcontents(); for (int i=0; i setrootdirectory("assets"); //mount the assets directory only, the user won't have to have "assets" in the filename to find things in it //to actually mount it getfilemanager()->mountfilesystem(pfilesystem); //test that it worked: fileinstance myfile("textfileinsideassetsdirofthezip.txt"); if (myfile.isloaded()) logmsg("marty, it worked!"); what about writing user data files? i just use fwrite and fread and haven't have any trouble with porting so far. as long as you use getsavepath() you're ok as far as file permissions go. proton/filemanager.txt · last modified: 2012/03/09 01:05 by seth page tools show pagesourceold revisionsbacklinksback to top except where otherwise noted, content on this wiki is licensed under the following license: cc attribution-share alike 4.0 international

__label__low stel een vraag startpagina oplossingen en welkom bij de karify helpdesk voor cliënten voer hier je zoekterm in.. zoeken maak je als zorgverlener gebruik van karify? ga dan naar de support pagina's startpagina oplossing help berichten hoe verstuur ik een bericht? gewijzigd op: do, 8 dec, 2016 at 2:32 pm met berichten in karify kun je in een veilige omgeving berichten versturen en ontvangen. ook kun je bestanden meesturen. maar hoe verstuur ik nou eigenlijk een bericht? ga via de navigatiebalk naar berichten: klik op de knop nieuw bericht rechtsboven in beeld: nu kun je een nieuw bericht typen. kies uit je contactlijst één of meerdere geadresseerden. ontvangers van het bericht zien altijd wie het bericht nog meer kunnen zien. zo weet je altijd wie de ontvangers zijn als je antwoordt. kies een kort en bondig onderwerp zodat de ontvanger direct weet waar het over gaat. in het tekstveld typ je je bericht. je hebt de mogelijkheid een bijlage aan je bericht toe te voegen. dit kan onderaan bij bijlage - voeg toe. zorg ervoor dat je in de begeleidende tekst duidelijk maakt wat je als bijlage meestuurt. was dit antwoord nuttig? ja nee hoe kunnen we dit artikel verbeteren? meer artikelen in berichten hoe verstuur ik een bericht? naar wie kan ik berichten versturen? bijlagen versturen en ontvangen mappen & favoriet e-consult afwezigheidsmelding karify 2017 algemene voorwaarden privacy en cookies
__label__low whatbreesees skip to content homebree upcoming shows past shows venues my jams friends with blogs tag archives: justin vernon december 26, 2017 · 9:16 pm bon iver friday, december 8, 2017 state theatre, portland, maine in a sentence–for me, sadly, this show was a surprising disappointment. i saw bon iver for the first time in september of 2012 at the bank of america pavillion in boston. caroline and i went together, and she wrote a lovely guest post giving the show a five star rating. i was in the third or fourth row for that full band show, and i was over the moon to hear some of my bon iver favorites in person and to sing “the wolves (acts i and ii)” together. the energy at that show was palpably positive. when i saw that bon iver was playing so nearby in portland at state theatre, i was thrilled. i set an alarm to buy tickets in the presale, but the timing of my teaching plans were a little off because we had an unexpected fire drill, so i selfishly asked my students to work on their homework for a few minutes while i tried to get tickets on both my laptop and my phone. my phone came through for me and i snagged a pair of tickets a few rows from the back of the room, and i can’t think of a time i was so happy to have basically back row seats. i checked again when tickets went on sale to the general public, but they seemed completely sold out right away. i read through more than a hundred comments from angry bon iver fans about how impossible it was to get tickets for the show, and revelled in my luck. i even looked online at stubhub just to see if i could get seats closer to the stage, but seats in my far away section were selling for $250 each (a huge markup over the $65 face value). i scoffed at the idea of selling my tickets for profit anyhow, but then i went to the show and thought twice. bartlett was my lucky date for the night, even though many people inquired about my extra ticket for the show right up until the night of the show. we met for dinner at el rayo, had a couple of tacos and cocktails, and made our way to state theatreearly to make it through their added security and because there was no opening act. justin vernon took the stage solo, which i am usually totally in favor of, but this was an odd night. i was surprised by how many people were back and forth to the bar and bathroom during the show because we’d all paid a decent amount for these highly sought after tickets and i figured everyone there would be a big fan. (a sarcastic shout out to the annoying super fan couple in the third row that spent most of the night dancing wildly on your feet–rudely obstructing the views of and distracting everyone all around you. you guys made me glad my seats were so far away). there was some sort of chatter coming from the other front orchestra section, i guess, because justin interjected a snarky comment about them, and then followed up with a comment about how we should all just love each other. later, someone from the crowd shouted out “i love you, justin,” and he responded “i have plans later. but i appreciate that.” i thought some (but not all) of his banter with the audience was awkward to the point of kind of mean spirited. it felt like he didn’t want to have to perform for us, and it ruined the show experience for me. my view of justin vernon from the back of the state theatre i didn’t feel at all this way five years ago when i first saw bon iver live, so i have some theories about this night’s cringeworthy moments. the easiest explanation would be that folks nearest him were being rude and i couldn’t hear it. that, sadly, has been the case at other shows i’ve been to in portland, where people talk all night over the performer. regina spektor’s show earlier this year at state theatrecomes right to mind. maybe something has shifted for justin during these years that makes performing difficult for him, or, he was just having a bad night. if i missed something, please tell me. i’d love to know there was an obvious cause for his somewhat grumpy demeanor. musically, justin was great. i loved hearing so many songs i love live–“flume,”“perth,”“blood bank,”“skinny love,”and “woods”–and his cover of“i can’t make you love me”was heart wrenching, as expected. i enjoyed hearing the heavily electronic songs from his 2016 album, 22, a million in person, too. it felt good to sing “the wolves (acts i and ii)” together to end the night at justin’s invitation, but i was very surprised he only played a one song encore (a cover of mahalia jackson’s “satisfied mind”), because he was on stage less than an hour. i’d felt so lucky to have the opportunity to be in the room, but was genuinely sadly disappointed during and after the show. it felt like an off night from start to finish, and it seemed to me like justin struggles with the pressures of being a beloved musician, which seemed to shine through during this show. in the end, i am fine with having spent $65 to see justin vernon from basically the back row, but i probably wouldn’t do it again, which is disappointing given how much his music has positively impacted my life. if you missed this show, i honestly don’t think you missed much. maybe something was going on with the crowd up front that i couldn’t hear. if folks were being rude and justin was annoyed with them–i can totally live with that. from where i sat, though, this show was a bummer. if you saw another night of this tour and had a very positive experience, i would also like to hear from you so that i know this was simply an off night and that justin is just fine. i’m truly hoping for that. xo, bree advertisements leave a comment filed under __label__low dialogue-abrahaml'équipe de "dialogue abraham" vous souhaite la bienvenue ! ce forum recherche avant tout une atmosphère cordiale et respectueuse, chacun s'efforçant d'écouter l'autre avec la même bienveillance qui doit accueillir son propre témoignage. nous travaillons à nous comprendre mutuellement en vérité, et non à entretenir des conflits. nous ne sommes pas parfaits, mais pensons qu'il est possible d'avoir des échanges de qualité sur les sujets religieux. puissiez-vous, vous qui venez ici, contribuer à cet effortdialogue-abrahamforum interreligieux du blog collectif judéo-islamo-chrétien créé le 10 février 2011accueil faq s'enregistrer connexion avertissement : les "sujets similaires" suggérés en bas de chaque discussion lorsque vous n'êtes pas connectés ne sont pas de notre responsabilité. il en va de même pour les publicités qui peuvent apparaître sous ce message. ces messages automatisés sont générés par notre hébergeur sans aucun contrôle de notre part. ils peuvent donc présenter des opinions opposées à nos valeurs et à celles des religions et philosophies représentées sur cet espace d'échange et de fraternité. merci de votre compréhension.musique et religiondialogue-abraham :: général :: débats générauxpage 2 sur 4 • partagez • page 2 sur 4 • 1, 2, 3, 4 re: musique et religion gilbert-michel le mer 18 mai - 17:23-ren- a écrit:gilbert-michel a écrit:je dirais parce que c'est le sacré qui "se dépose" là où le vouloir humain s'efface devant la volonté de dieupour vous, le sacré est présent dans cet air profane de bellini ?dans son interprétation !gilbert-michelmessages : 1088date d'inscription : 13/02/2011 la musique en islam... isabelle le sam 10 déc - 18:29voici le fil pour discuter du statut de la musique en islam.la musique est strictement interdite en islam. c'est la parole du diable.dans ce cas, écouter le klaxon d'une voiture c'est également interdit : c'est de la musique !ecouter le bip sonore avant de poster un message, c'est également interdit, ça a été créé avec des instruments de musique.ecouter la petite musique de windows quand tu démarres ton ordinateur, c'est également interditecouter le clic d'une souris, c'est également interdit.ecouter le bruit des touches quand tu tapes sur un clavier, c'est interdit.ecouter le passage d'un train ou le bruit des voitures, c'est interdit.et certaines personnes ont vraiment une voix mélodieuse, c'est interdit de les écouter ?isabellemessages : 948réputation : 0date d'inscription : 19/10/2011 chant du coran hannat le dim 11 déc - reviews cuisines: mexican restaurant details drcheesela junta, colorado14346reviewed july 19, 2012 mexican in n. michiganwhen in petoskey i go to jose's. the food is fresh, especially the pico de gallo and guacamole. they have the best chile rellenos in the state as far as i'm concerned (unless you make them homemade). the place is casual and the staff friendly. i don't give it an "excellent" because while the food is worth the price you have to pay extra for chips. i think free salsa & chips isn't too much to ask for. but...i'll keep going back!valueatmosphereservicefoodask drcheese about __label__low メニュー 全在庫車両一覧 新着情報一覧 公式ブログ 公式ブログ一覧 オーダー販売（新車/中古車） 自動車整備/メンテナンス アメ車・逆輸入車の車検 アメ車・逆輸入車のカスタム その他 お客様の声 車買取査定 フェアライン情報 フェアラインについて 会社概要 ショップ案内 スタッフ紹介 採用求人情報 個人情報取扱 お問い合わせ 2014 10nov 工場ブログ tweet どうも工場の土川です。今日も朝からいつも以上にきれいにしました。工場の床を積極的に手伝ってくれる早川さん。ありがとうございます。やりましたね。いい笑顔です。こんな感じで今日の朝は始まりました。では作業を見ていきます。納車点検中のタンドラやっていきます。オイル変えていきます。まずはエンジンオイル抜きます。エレメント変えます。エレメントは下の蓋をとってエレメント内のオイルを抜いてからとります。こうすればオイルで汚れません。フロントデフオイル抜きます。入れるのはここからオイルがあふれてくるまで入れます。オートマオイルまず下のドレンを取ってオイル出してそのあとにオイルパンとってきれいにしてからつけます。リヤデフオイルフロントと同様で上のドレンからでてくるまで入れます。あとはこの前変えたパット見にくいですがフロントもリヤも新品です。これはフロントです。画像ないですがベルトテンショナーも新品に。特に悪いとこもなくいい状態です。見えない所もきれいにして納車します。次は在庫タンドラのステップ交換です。右側がへこんでます。左右交換です。重いので輸出部隊マイガが手伝ってくれました。こんな感じに裏でネジ８本でとまってるだけなので簡単にとれます。物は一緒ではないですがきれいになりましたね。最後に新しいオイルが入りました。ジョージルブクラシックカーにマッチングしたエンジンオイル２０ｗ－５０です。４? ５８００円１? ２３００円フェアラインで売っていますのでぜひ使ってみてください。では今日はこの辺りで ｔｕｎｄｒａ等々、お預かり！ 納車＆納車準備 facebookにも最新情報を掲載中です！ 株式会社フェアライン recommended blogs フェアラインツーリングイベント お疲れ様です。 10月最初のブログになりました。 今日は昼から少し雨が降り なんか久しぶりの雨なよう… 工場ブログ どうも工場の土川です。この前の水曜日にフェアラインで海に行ってきました。船も乗せてもらって、楽しくｂｂｑできてよかったです。そんな… 2015ｙ tundra リフトアップ お疲れ様です。今日は寒い・・・昼からは雪が降ってまいりました。明日の午前中まで雪が降るらしいですよ・・・まぁみなさん運… 工場ブログ どうも工場の土川です。だんだんと寒くなってきて冬に近づいてきましたね。この前まで暑かったのに時間が経つのがはやく感じます。寒くなり… 愛知県豊橋市 s様 08y tahoe ltz 4wd アメ車デビューを専門店に任せて良かったです。フェアラインに任せて良かったです。いや、横家さんに任せて良かったです。お世話になりまし… 愛知県春日井市ｔ様 17y vellfire goldeneyes 数年後にまたアメ車に帰ってきます！ … facebookでも最新情報を購読出来ます。 株式会社フェアライン news＆topics 2018/4/9 18y tahoe,11ytundra 2018/3/29 18y sequoia,05y dodge ram 2018/3/23 18y explorer,18y sienna 過去の記事 最近の投稿 2018.04.19 ４月１日に無事、我が家にセコイアが納車されました‼️色々、問題はありましたが、終わりよければ全て良し… 2018.04.19 お疲れ様です。 今週は休みを頂き、羽を伸ばしに グランピングに行ってきました。 … 2018.04.17 こんにちは、山田です～(^^)/ ワンオクのライブに行ってきました‼ 地元ナゴヤ… 2018.04.17 とても最高の車とケアに満足しています！ 次回もfairlineで購入したいです！… 2018.04.16 お疲れ様です。 4月も半ば、あと2週間ほどでゴールデン ウィークですね！ フェアラインは定休日… 公式ブログ：カテゴリ一覧 お客様の声 (459) オーダー販売（新車/中古車） (417) 自動車整備/メンテナンス (447) アメ車・逆輸入車の車検 (423) アメ車・逆輸入車のカスタム (560) その他 (795) 未分類 __label__low see all stores cars for sale sell your car financing articles 7 best small trucks for 2018 best-selling cars 7 best small trucks for 2018 published friday, april 13, 2018 01 the right combination of ruggedness and style. a pickup truck is a practical vehicle option for many drivers. at the same time, larger pickup trucks can sometimes be a little "over-the-top" for basic hauling, towing, and cargo needs. this is where shopping for small pickup trucks can be a wise option. with a smaller sized or midsize pickup truck, you can still enjoy substantial towing capacity and cargo storage—along with greater fuel economy and maneuverability in even the smallest of urban spaces. in many ways, small pickup trucks offer the best of both worlds! looking for some help in narrowing down your options when it comes to a small truck purchase? we've already taken care of some of the research for you. this list of seven top small trucks was developed based on vehicle type and carmax sales data from september 29, 2017 through march 29, 2018. here are our findings: ford explorer sport trac honda ridgeline ford ranger gmc canyon chevrolet colorado nissan frontier toyota tacoma 07 ford explorer sport trac first created in 2001 as an offshoot of the popular ford explorer suv, the ford explorer sport trac is similar in body style to the explorer suv with the addition of a small pickup bed in the back. and while this particular vehicle was only manufactured until 2010 (with a year off in 2006), it reached peak popularity in the small truck market due to its innovation (especially for its time) and functionality. if you're feeling a little torn between an suv and a pickup truck for your next vehicle, the sport trac might be a good compromise for you. and despite the fact that it hasn't been in production in awhile, you can generally still find used sport tracs on the market, particularly in the 2007 through 2010 model years. 06 honda ridgeline if you're intrigued by the idea of an suv/pickup crossover but are looking for something with more recent production, the honda ridgeline is definitely worth a test drive. the 2017 version of this vehicle boasts a unique two-way tailgate that is even wider and longer than that of most midsize pickup trucks. it also comes standard with a powerful 3.5 liter v6 engine, though upgraded engine options are available as you move up in trim level. speaking of trim options, the 2017 ridgeline is available in an impressive range of seven trims, including the base rt, sport, rtl-e, and premium black edition. standard features across all trim levels include a rearview camera, tow hitch, and 18-inch wheels. 05 ford ranger originally manufactured from 1983 through 2011, the ford ranger consistently topped lists for best-selling small pickup trucks. in 2019, ford will bring back the ranger with a brand new redesign that many are eagerly anticipating. in the meantime, you can still find used ford rangers on the market, such as the popular 2011 ranger. this small pickup truck is available in both a regular and extended cab, known as the supercab, for additional passenger leg room. the 2011 ranger also comes in both a six-foot and seven-foot bed option to suit your hauling needs, and is available in three trim levels: the xl, xlt, and sport. a 2.3 liter, 143-horsepower engine comes standard, though an upgraded v6 is an option on the xlt and sport trims. 04 gmc canyon looking for a pickup truck with a little more cabin space than some of these smaller pickups on the market? if so, then the gmc canyon is a great midsize pickup option worth your consideration. the 2017 version of this truck is available in your choice of two-, four-, or -five-seater options, as well as two different bed lengths and five trim options to choose from: the base sl, canyon, sle, slt, and premium denali. standard features across all trim levels include a 2.5 liter, four cylinder engine, rearview camera, and 4.2-inch color display. and in its upgraded v6 engine, you'll enjoy a maximum towing capacity of 7,000 pounds (versus 3,500 pounds with the standard engine). 03 chevrolet colorado another excellent midsize pickup truck to consider is the chevrolet colorado. this truck has been one of the best-selling pickups on the market for many years, and for good reason. the 2017 colorado boasts impressive maneuverability and handling, especially when compared to its full-size counterpart (the silverado). it is also available with a wide range of customization options that buyers will love, including three engine choices, several different bed configurations, two bed lengths, and a whopping five trim levels. in the base trim, drivers will enjoy an extended cab, rearview camera, and 2.5 liter engine. upgrade to the lt trim, however, and you'll also enjoy an available 4g wi-fi hot spot! 02 nissan frontier when it comes to midsize pickup trucks that are both practical and affordable, the nissan frontier is a strong contender. while it may not be loaded with standard features, the 2017 frontier is a rugged work truck that will serve many drivers well. offered in both a crew cab and extended cab, as well as a 5-foot or 6.1-foot bed length, this frontier comes in your choice of five trim levels. standard on the base s trim are rear privacy glass, bluetooth® connectivity, and 15-inch wheels. in order to upgrade from the base four cylinder engine (and 3,500-pound towing capacity, when properly equipped1), however, you'll need to select the sv or higher trim (which comes with a v6 capable of towing nearly double that when the vehicle is properly equipped). 01 toyota tacoma topping our list of best small pickup trucks is the toyota tacoma. looking at the 2017 tacoma, drivers love its high profile and abundant standard features, which include a durable composite bed (no liner needed!), a backup camera, and even a built-in gopro® mount on the windshield for easy recording. these ample features, combined with its towing capacity of nearly 7,000 pounds (when properly equipped1) and incredibly smooth ride, make the tacoma a top-seller in smaller pickups. false true new arrival shop used small trucks near you start your search основе карт сервисов яндекс и google. мы рады, что наш сервис оказался вам полезен и вы смогли узнать как проехать на автомобиле из пункта тамбов (россия) в пункт рабочий посёлок таловая (россия). район, воронежская область составляет 230.5 км. время поездки 4 часов, 58 минутбез учета пробок и времени на отдых и питание расход топлива 23 л.при расходе 10 литров на 100 километров затраты на __label__low mumblings from 203cm above earth this is the blog of steve davis. that is all. tuesday, january 24, 2006 much better day today was a much better day overall with much lower levels of anxiety and depression. i had a call back from the nlp practitioner and will arrange to do a course of 5 evening sessions with her at the end of february. she's convinced that nlp will definately help. i have to admit to being a little sceptical but will give anything a go. oh my god! i decided to try something different at the gym today and had a go at a body combat class. i'm not sure what i was expecting, perhaps a cross between martial arts and music but it was way more intense than anything i could have prepared for. it combined a very high energy dance workout with martial arts and combat moves, punches and kicks. it uses a completely different set of muscles than spinning and highlighted to me how little co-ordination i have. it took a little while to get into the flow and more often than not i was completely out of sync with everyone else but after about 20 minutes i got into the flow. i'll definately give it another go. i think i'm going to feel it tomorrow though :-) posted by steve at 21:29 no comments: post a comment newer post older post home subscribe to: post comments (atom) 1000 miles in 2012 this work is licensed under a creative commons attribution-noncommercial-no derivative works 3.0 license. my links garans blog my ebay auctions my flickr photos www.flickr.com this is a flickr badge showing public photos from stevedavis. make your own badge here. post labels blog car comments computers diet entertainment fun motorbike personal photos rants reviews travel work blog archive ► 2012 (4) ► april (1) ► january (3) ► 2010 (3) ► june (1) ► may (2) ► 2009 (14) ► december (1) ► november (1) ► september (1) ► june (2) ► march (1) ► february (3) ► january (5) ► 2008 (90) ► december (4) ► november (3) ► october (9) ► september (10) ► august (6) ► july (14) ► june (6) ► may (16) ► april (6) ► march (9) ► february (3) ► january (4) ► 2007 (58) ► december (2) ► november (4) ► october (2) ► september (10) ► august (4) ► july (6) ► june (2) ► may (6) ► april (3) ► march (12) ► february (4) ► january (3) ▼ 2006 (62) ► december (3) ► november (2) ► october (2) ► september (1) ► august (5) ► july (4) ► june (5) ► may (5) ► april (5) ► march (10) ► february (5) ▼ january (15) at last! efter en stund där blev jag akut trött så en kollega körde hem mig. det är något som jag har märkt efter operationen är att jag när jag blir trött så blir jag akut trött och måste bara komma hem om jag är borta så i em så har jag vilat. denna underbara "korg" fick jag av fritsla if's styrelse. tack snälla 💖 ikväll hade vi verkligen fredagsmys 😍gud vad gott det var...algot kämpar med en krabbklo joel visar stolt upp sin krabbklo permalink | kommentarer (1) | trackbacks hemma 😃 12 november 2015 | 18:57 i går gjorde jag inget alls, låg i soffan hela dagen verkligen var frusen och vad passar inte bättre än att dricka te då. det ser inte mö ut men fasiken vad det kliar, äter allergimedicin och det lindrar det en hel del. när familjen var på ingång så fixade jag till lite mat, inget avancerat men gott. vanlig potatis och sötpotatis i ugnen, stekt kycklingfile med en sås gjort på yoghurt, vitlök, salt, paprikapulver och peppar (skulle även varit spiskummin men det hade vi inte) några armband pärlade jag oxå. så kul att ni är så många som har beställt. tack 😍idag kom min kusin och han lilla dotter natalie hit. en mysig stund med lek, fika och mat. idag skulle jag tagit influensa sprutan oj jisses vilken kö..efter 30 min så ropades nummer 23 upp och jag hade 69...hallå jag vände och gick ut. fick denna bok av min kusin och hans familj. ska bli väldigt intressant att läsa den. kanske skulle ta och lägga mig snart och börja läsa den. permalink | kommentarer (2) | trackbacks utskriven 10 november 2015 | 22:32 tittar bara in snabbt för att berätta att jag idag blev utskriven 😃😃 så skönt att få sova hemma och dela min familjs vardag, var ett bra tag sedan jag gjorde det. att se joels min när jag kom och hämta honom på förskolan värmde så mycket ❤ sådan glädje och sedan när han fick veta att jag även skulle sova hemma visste han inte riktigt vart han skulle ta vägen. när jag hämtade algot, tittade han på mig och frågade -vad gör du här mamma? lilla prins. nu ska här sovas....natti 💓 permalink | kommentarer (14) | trackbacks om ann-sofi sök i bloggen senaste inläggen nya besked bra besked 😃 en tuff dag dålig... trött och orkeslös alla hjärtansdag dagen för новости науки и техники достижения it hi tech космонавтики электротехники интернета культура авто новинки тв наука культура 5 канала 1 канала новости онлайн прогноз и ставка на игру химки – барселона 29 декабря 2017 в спортивная аналитика и новости спорта: статистика матчей и прогнозы декабрь 27, 2017 0 41 просмотров дата игры 29.12.2017 начало через 1 дн 23 ч 30 мин 1дн 23:30 г 29 декабря 2017 года в 20:00 по московскому времени в рамках 15-го тура регулярного сезона мужской баскетбольной евролиги подмосковные «химки» примут каталонскую «барселону». химки «химки», как для середняка европейского баскетбола, вполне сносно проводит евросезон, как раз замыкая топ-8 и претендуя на плэй-офф, правда, та же «баскония» позади всего в одной победе. подмосковная команда далека от своих лучших кондиций, выиграв только в пяти матчах из последних 13-ти. а вот на своей арене «химки» оказывались победителями в 3-х последних случаях. конкретно в евролиге дома они выиграли в 6-ти матчах из 7-ми. во внутреннем первенстве «химки» идут 5-ми, выиграв в 5-ти матчах из 8-ми, что позволяет чувствовать себя спокойно, ведь 9-й «енисей» они уже опережают на 3 виктории. в последнем своём матче «химки» в гостях в рамках евролиги проиграли цска – 79:68. уступая в 17 пунктов походу матча, гости сокращали счёт до всего «-1», но на большее их не хватило. барселона у каталонцев дела намного хуже – они выиграли всего 4 матча из 14-ти возможных, уже на 4 виктории отставая от топ-8. команда находится в глубоком кризисе, проиграв последние 6 матчей кряду. а на выезде победили только в 4-х матчах из последних 13-ти. в национальном чемпионате дела у них идут получше – промежуточное 4-е место и фора в 2 победы над 9-й командой пока позволяют им чувствовать себя уверенно. в последнем своём матче в рамках евролиги они проиграли в гостях «басконии» — 85:82. к концу 3-й четверти гости проигрывали 21 очко, но менее чем за минуту до конца матча даже вышли на 1 пункт вперёд, но сил отстоять преимущество им не хватило. химки — барселона: статистика личных встреч команды играли друг с другом 4 раза, выиграв каждая по два раза у себя на площадке. причём оба раза победы были разгромными в прошлом сезоне – 75:61 –в химках и 87:70 – в каталонии. котировки букмекерских контор бк «пари матч» фаворитом матча считает «химки», на победу которых можно поставить с коэффициентом 1,54 против 15,4 на ничью и 2,74 – на победу «барселоны». основная фора измеряется 4,5 очками, а тотал насчитывает 161,5 пункт. прогноз и ставка от betonmobile.ru «химки» играют лучше, особенно на своём паркете. у «барселоны» очень плохая форма и неудачная серия, более того, эта команда исторически плохо играет с «химками» на выезде и наверняка уже собирается сосредоточиться на выступлениях в чемпионате испании. победа «химок» с форой (-4,5 очка) за 1,92 подробности на: betonmobile.ru 2017-12-27 novostivse предыдущий цымбалюк-романовская хочет помириться с джигарханяном следующий прогноз и ставка на матч кротоне – наполи 29 декабря 2017 читайте также атлетик — валенсия и еще два футбольных матча: экспресс дня на 28 февраля 2018 февраль 28, 2018 5 самых громких отказов в выплате выигрышей в букмекерских конторах февраль 28, 2018 продавцы догов и еще 4 типа мошенников в букмекерском бизнесе февраль 27, 2018 эспаньол — реал и еще два футбольных матча: экспресс дня на 27 февраля 2018 февраль 27, 2018 прогноз ставка на матч боруссия д – аугсбург 26 февраля 2018 февраль 26, 2018 боруссия д — аугсбург и еще два футбольных матча: экспресс дня на 26 февраля 2018 февраль 26, 2018 __label__low recent entries friends archive profile add to friends rss green_life зеленые решения для всей семьи. green life биткоин "зеленее", чем вы думали green_lifedecember 11th, 2017сегодня мир словно помешался на криповалютах и на их майнинге. но в свою очередь «зеленые», на фоне криптолихорадки, озабочены вопросами экологии, ведь всем известно, что один только майнинг биткоина расходует такое количество электроэнергии, которое превышает потребление целых государств, например, ирландии, дании или японии.однако, bloomberg считает, что ситуация с огромным расходом электроэнергии несколько надуманна. и вместо того, чтобы беспокоиться о том, как скоро биткоин растопит полярные ледяные шапки, стоит подумать, сколько энергии может быть спасено.прежде чем рассказать, что же имел ввиду в своей статье «блумберг», давайте разберемся, как же происходит майнинг и почему он требует столько электроэнергии. цифровая валюта на самом деле вещь весьма расточительная. биткоин-майнеры, которые обрабатывают транзакции в обмен на криптовалюту, становятся участниками большой гонки, в которой решаются чрезвычайно сложные криптографические головоломки. это вычислительное бремя помогает сохранить безопасность транзакций – превратив в непосильную задачу их подделку, - но этот процесс также требует от майнеров строительства гигантских «ферм» с серверами, которые потребляют огромное количество энергии. чем более ценным становится биткоин, тем больше майнеров готово тратить деньги на оборудование и электричество.и вот на какую мысль наталкивает нас «блумберг»: он пишет о том, что на многие вещи, в том числе и на биткоин стоит смотреть в перспективе. недавний отчет показывает, при текущих ценах майнинговые фермы «добывающие» bitcoin будут потреблять приблизительно 8,27 тераватт-часов в год. эта цифра может показаться огромной, но на самом деле это гораздо меньше, чем используют центры обработки данных в сша, и только около 0,21 процента от общего потребления электроэнергии в штатах. сам же биткоин выгодно отличается от других валют и товаров, и даже может помочь заменить некоторые из них: мировое производство наличных денег и монет потребляет около 11 тераватт-часов в год, в то время как добыча золота сжигает эквивалент 132 тераватт-часов. и эти цифры не включают в себя производство и использование бронированных грузовиков, банковских хранилищ, систем безопасности и тому подобное. поэтому в правильном контексте биткоин можно назвать «зеленым».более того потребление электроэнергии для майнинга биткоина не обязательно будет расти, как сейчас. например, уже сегодня дата-центры, где и располагаются майнинговые мощности, стали намного лучше. недавно министерство энергетики сша предсказывало, что потребление ими электроэнергии будет удваиваться каждые пять лет. но, в последние годы, общее потребление электроэнергии дата-центрами наоборот стало уменьшаться даже несмотря на то, что число майнинговых ферм и, соответственно, появление таких центров продолжало расти. как оказалось, улучшенная технология охлаждения и управления питанием повысила эффективность. биткоин-майнеры не менее мотивированы экономить, поэтому совершенно очевидно, что они будут стремиться стать более эффективными и использовать самую дешевую и доступную энергию, которую обычно дают гидроэлектростанции и другие возобновляемые источники энергии.легко критиковать биткоин за то, что он расточительно использует электроэнергию. но в жизни так много вещей, включая самолеты, поездки на работу и в другие страны, которые забирают энергию в гораздо больших масштабах, мы просто об этом не задумываемся, привыкнув критиковать все новое. биткоин как криптовалюта на самом деле может дать много преимуществ. как насчет возможности свободно отправлять деньги в любую точку мира без каких-либо разрешений или третьих лиц, таких как банк? или владеть активом, который не может быть захвачен? люди в сша и других развитых странах могут считать это само собой разумеющимся, но люди в таких государствах, как зимбабве и венесуэла, хватаются за биткоин как за спасительную соломинку, которая может дать им надежду на выживание. поэтому, возможно, все эти затраты на сложные вычислительные процессы не расточительны: может быть, майнеры превращают энергию в нечто более ценное.источник: bitcoin, биткоин, криптовалюта :( leave a comment ) archive __label__low becoming what we already are… a weblog about faith, life and stuff menu skip to content 12 apr 200912 apr 2009 pdbb now what? what's next? where shall we boldly go?? the title of today’s posting “now what?” is a very good question being as this is still easter. in fact, just a little fyi for ya here… easter lasts 50 days…up to pentecost. this not a season in the church year, like sundays in advent or what have you… we have 50 days of easter. do you think you can make your left over ham and jelly beans stretch that far? seriously, i ask…”now what?” because i started this blog as an exercise to go along with devotions about 60 of us at st. john did during lent. my question to you if you are in fact reading this… is “now what?” i think i have gotten in to a groove with this and i think i will continue. that being said i would love to hear from you about what you would like to see here. if you have questions we could pursue together, or directions or topics we might explore i would love to hear about them. leave a comment and let me know won’t ya? one final “what’s next?” christians confess that jesus is our risen lord, so now that christ is raised “what’s next?” maybe a fair question for us to ask ourselves each day! easter blessings. christ has risen! he has risen indeed! alleluia! advertisements share this:facebookgoogletwittertumblrpinterestemaillinkedinmoreprintredditlike this:like loading... related uncategorized published by pdbb just a guy who loves his callings in life as a father, husband, lutheran pastor and geek, nerd, or techno-whatever.. take a look at the gravatar, it is um... nearly spot on which is just a little spooky. view all posts by pdbb post navigation previous easternext gobsmacked leave a reply cancel reply enter your comment here... fill in your details below or click an icon to log in: email (required) (address never made public) name (required) website you are commenting using your wordpress.com account. __label__low pilotepro.fr - aventure d'un pilote français au québec bonjour à tous(tes). vous pouvez lire sur ce blog mon histoire racontée jours après jours durant ma vie au québec, ainsi que des photos et vidéos de mes vols durant ma formation de pilote. ceci me permet de vous présenter pas à pas mon évolution, et de vous faire partager mon métier et ma passion: l'aviation transport canada and faa cpl/me/ir/fi atpl jaa réussi 1200h total, 1050h pic, 700h fi home ajouter à mes favoris. me contacter niagara falls tour 2 sept-îles spotting 1er solo test en vol cpl test en vol ifr québec 10 médévac ma région la gaspésie samedi 14 novembre 2009 un vol particulier... il y a quelques semaines une famille appelle ma compagnie pour faire un "vol coqueluche". mais qu'est-ce donc ?la coqueluche est une maladie très contagieuse due à une bactérie du nom de bordetella pertussis (incroyable les recherches que l'on peut faire sur le net !). elle se caractérise par de violentes quintes de toux suivies d’une respiration difficile appelée « chant du coq ».le « vol de coqueluche » ou « méthode strasbourgeoise » a été inventé dans la première moitié du xxe siècle par le docteur matter pour soigner la coqueluche.son principe est le suivant : monter le plus rapidement possible entre 9500 pieds et 11 500 pieds d'altitude dans un avion non pressurisé, y rester une cinquantaine de minutes, redescendre aussi rapidement que possible, en respectant un palier à 5000 pieds.pourquoi, en avion non pressurisé, les malades retrouvaient-ils leur vitalité ?qui dit « brutale ascension » dit « raréfaction de l’oxygène », ce qui entraîne un changement de pression au niveau du sang. les molécules d’oxyhémoglobine (qui ça ?), transporteuses de l’oxygène dans le sang, relâchent cet élément en plus grande quantité qu’à l’ordinaire. cette libération accrue d’oxygène a des conséquences très positives sur la vitalité.ce procédé permet, non pas d’avoir plus d’oxygène, ce qui serait dangereux, mais d’utiliser au mieux l’oxygène de l’air naturellement disponible, sans danger et sans effets secondaires.cette technique optimise l’action des médicaments et lutte contre leur possible effets secondaires.j'ai donc fait ce vol pour le moins étrange à première vu, mais qui finalement a peut-être guéri cette mère et ces 3 enfants âgés d'environ 4 ans. (n'ayant pas eut de retour je suppose qu'ils vont mieux :))on se serait cru dans un épisode de dr. house, mes passagers et moi-mêmes ayant des masques médicaux stériles, légèrement effrayant pour les enfants, en pleur durant la totalité du vol !le vol a été plutôt plaisant pour moi, en c-182rg turbo, la montée à 11 500 pieds s'est faite en 10 minutes environ, une altitude où je n'ai pas le droit d'y rester plus de 30min sans apport d'oxygène supplémentaire. j'ai du redescendre quelques instants à 9 500' avant d'y remonter pour une vingtaine de minutes encore.quant à la descente qui doit être rapide... elle l'a été !environ 4000' / minutes, au grand "non-bonheur" des oreilles de mes passagers malades, pour qui j'ai du ralentir cette descente !en tout cas, cette journée là restera une expérience parmi les autres, et à 11 500' l'air est pur, et tout parait petit, surtout les hommes... publié par juju à 23:47 3 commentaires articles plus récents articles plus anciens accueil inscription à : articles (atom) qui suis-je ? julien, né à nice, pilote professionnel, instructeur de vol tcca et faacpl/ir/fi/me/atpl ambiance... mon logbook au 17/03/2010 mes récits ... ► 2011 (1) ► août (1) ► 2010 (3) ► octobre (1) ► mars (1) ► février (1) ▼ 2009 (15) ▼ novembre (1) un vol particulier... ► septembre (2) ► juillet (2) ► juin (2) ► mai (2) ► avril (3) ► mars (2) ► février (1) ► 2008 (53) ► décembre (4) ► novembre (5) ► octobre (5) ► septembre (4) ► août (5) ► juillet (5) ► juin (5) ► mai (5) ► avril (5) ► mars (4) ► février (5) ► janvier (1) ► 2007 (36) ► décembre (2) ► novembre (5) ► octobre (7) ► septembre (1) ► août (3) ► juillet (2) ► mai (3) ► avril (1) ► mars (4) ► février (4) ► janvier (4) photo du jour mes liens favoris rollinks transfers au pays de l'azur... blog de steve danny's news... le blog de fabien le blog de jj le blog de mon ami tributaire :-) le meilleur de l'aviation suivre par email :-) visiteurs ... compteur

__label__low search this site: home eligibility »· application process services » · sf access · taxi & ramp taxi service · shop-a-round rules & policies fare information » · sf access · taxi & ramp taxi service · shop-a-round resources news employment opportunities contact us » sf accesssf access fare informationfares sf access service costs a certified rider $2.50 per one-way trip. all riders are required to pay the driver either in cash (exact change please) or with a single ride ticket that costs $2.50 each and may be purchased from the san francisco paratransit office in whatever quantity needed. these ride tickets do not expire. when purchasing sf access ride tickets by mail, please allow sufficient time to receive the tickets. sf access fares must be paid upon boarding and are subject to change. companions as a certified rider, you may arrange to bring one (1) companion or guest with you on each ride for $2.50 per ride, per companion. fares for companions may also be paid using ride tickets available from the san francisco paratransit office. you may add additional fare paying companions to your trip only on a same day, space available basis. please check with your provider on the day of service whether these arrangements can be made. you will need to verify that there is space available on both trips if you would like the addtional companions to accompany you on a round trip. attendants an attendant is someone who provides assistance you need in order to complete the requested trip or at your destination. typically, an attendant provides specialized assistance that the driver is unable to provide or assists the rider with activities of daily living at the destination. if you have been certified as needing an attendant, the attendant may ride with you at no additional charge. the attendant can ride in addition to any companion you may be taking. both attendants and companions must start and end their travel at the same address as the certified rider. some content on this page is saved in an alternative format, adobe acrobat. to view these files, download the following free software: adobe® reader® home page · services · sf access · taxi ramp taxi services · shop-a-round · fare informationabout us · resources · contact us · news page · doing business with sf paratransit · partnerstemplate_fare-info-sfaccess.php

driving related question: * leave this field blank: free dmv practice tests > 6 high way driving tips for new drivers the daily driver / blog 6 high way driving tips for new drivers 1. pay careful attention to the speed limit ever drive down the highway, only to see a vehicle that is moving at a ridiculously slow speed such as 40mph? what they are doing is illegal on many highways, as there is usually a minimum speed of 45mph required on such highways. driving too slowly poses a hazard not only to you, but also to everyone else using that highway. plus, it's annoying to everyone, and you could be ticketed for it. on the other hand, the speed limit on most highways is 70mph during the day, and 65mph during the night. once again, the speed limit varies from highway to highway, as there are some that don't get very much traffic at all, and therefore the limit is slightly increased for these places. 2. stay in the right lane keep a close eye on any signs that may read "left lane for passing only", as these are especially common in states such as texas. contrary to popular belief, not all highways dedicate the left lane as the "fast" lane, as there are some highways that dedicate these left lanes strictly as passing lanes. it is acceptable to use these left lanes for passing, but not to use them continuously for cruising. move off to a lane on the right immediately after you are finished passing a car. such passing lanes are also more common on larger, multi-lane highways. failure to abide by this rule can result in a fine as high as $200 in the state of texas. 3. stay alert for trucks on the highway trucks can sometimes weigh up to 40 tons, and require up to 100 yards to come to a complete stop. one good piece of advice is to keep a safe distance behind trucks by watching when the truck in front of you passes a fixed object, then, seeing if it takes you at least two seconds to pass that same object. if it takes less than two seconds for you to pass that same object, you are driving too closely to that truck. also, don't try to nudge your way between a truck and the curb, as it is a horrendously bad idea. trucks make wide right turns, having several blind spots up to 200 feet behind their trailer, or up to 20 feet in front of the tractor. in other words, they may not see you. a good rule of thumb is that if you can't see the driver's windows or the actual truck driver, then they cannot see you. lastly, never pass a truck from behind when it is in reverse. 4. moving over for emergency vehicles many people naturally move an extra lane away from a stopped emergency vehicle that has bright red flashing lights. this is a correct maneuver, as the law requires you to do this. however, did you know that it is usually also required that you go 20mph below the posted speed limit as you do so? in states such as texas, you could receive a fine of $200 for not following these two rules. tips for road trips and longer drives 5. taking a break being drowsy can be downright deadly when driving on a highway, or anywhere for that matter. driver fatigue is an obvious indication that you are not alert enough to drive safely. if you suddenly find yourself yawning incessantly, drifting unintentionally from lane to lane, or find your eyelids closing intermittently due to tiredness, then pull over to a safe place, and stretch your legs. rest for 15-20 minutes, and repeat this every two hours or so, or better yet, just take a short nap in a safe place, if possible. the best way to combat driver fatigue is to simply prevent it beforehand by preparing yourself. get plenty of rest before a long drive, and avoid any drinking from midnight to 6 o'clock. even tiny amounts of alcohol are enough to influence your reaction time when driving. 6. rest areas are your friend large rest areas are places where you can park your car in a safe environment, and they almost always have law enforcement present. use these places to your advantage as a place of rest, using the bathroom, checking out road conditions, or learning about local points of interest. driving tips highway driving new drivers teen drivers more to explore motorcycle lane spliting on the highway teen driving privileges top riding tips for first-time motorcycle owners teen drinking and driving comments view the discussion thread. save money on car insurance now! enter __label__low cgc events recipes photos cornell gourmet club welcome to the blog of the cornell gourmet club january 13, 2011 digging the pig posted by elliesbelly under main courses leave a comment nine- hour roasted pork shoulder, from the new york times there is something truly magical about pork. whether it’s in heavenly bacon form or shredded on a sandwich with barbecue sauce, i really dig the pig. and for a chilly place like ithaca, comforting and meltingly tender pork shoulder is just the ticket. it’s a relatively inexpensive, tough, and somewhat gnarly-looking piece of meat from the shoulder of a pig, and can come with a fat cap on top that is best left on to baste the meat as it cooks. i first tried making pork shoulder, or boston butt as some say, one summer when i had little else to do. my goal was to tackle pulled pork over our little kettle grill but ended up getting impatient with the ten pounds of meat and took it off the heat much too early. my parents smiled politely but i knew it didn’t taste right. i looked up more recipes and found that secret to that beautiful meat you can cut with a spoon is a low temperature and a lot of time. i set to work and found new ways to prepare the cut – it’s adaptable to all kinds of cuisines, and can add a porky punch to soups and stews where it is not necessarily the main attraction. here are a few of my favorites: – swap one inch cubes of pork shoulder for beef in a chili recipe, simmering for 2-2 1/2 hours until tender (yields easily to a fork) – cook the same one inch cubes catalan-style with smoked paprika, green olives, onions and tomatoes until tender for a satisfying winter stew (thanks food and wine mag!) – braise cubes in a thai-style broth with coconut milk, chicken stock, lemongrass, thai curry paste, and lime until tender; serve over rice – pat a 5 to 6 pound cut with barbecue spice rub and cook low and slow in a 225 degree oven for 6 to 7 hours, shredding and serving with barbecue sauce and buns for a crowd – for the nyt roasted pork shoulder in the image above, turn the oven down to 200 and rub a 7 to 8 pound pork shoulder with olive oil, salt, and pepper. roast for 9 to 10 hours until pork can be shredded easily with a fork. serve with salsa verde, recipe at or with a homemade specialty of your own. the above roasted shoulder recipe came from a group dinner held by a cooking school in los angeles, called the “pork dinner.” that’s something i could make the trip for! hopefully, on a cold ithaca weekend a real live pig dinner will be coming to an apartment near you. advertisements share this:emailfacebookprintlike this:like loading... related leave a reply cancel reply enter your comment here... fill in your details below or click an icon to log in: email (required) (address never made public) name (required) website you are commenting using your wordpress.com account.
